<F P=106> [Article by V. G. Vishnevskiy, Yu. F. Vilesov, N. A. </F>
Groshenko, V. F. Lamekin, A. V. Yarygin; UDC 535.42;621.397] 
  [Abstract]A description is given of a spatial-light 
modulator based on magneto-optical epitaxial films of 
iron-garnet with planar anisotropy. The impact which a 
dielectric mirror has on the intensity distribution in a 
spectral plane is also described. The dielectric mirror, which 
possesses polarization selecting properties, allows single pass 
magneto-optical diffraction to be achieved. 2 figures, 1 table 
and 10 references. 

